\subsection{Field of values of a Dirichlet character}
\begin{definition}\label{character.dirichlet.value_field}
\uses{character.dirichlet.order}
The **field of values** of a Dirichlet character $\chi\colon\Z\to\C$ is the field $\Q(\chi(\Z))$ generated by its values; it is equal to the cyclotomic field $\Q(\zeta_n)$, where $n$ is the {{KNOWL('character.dirichlet.order', 'order')}} of $\chi$.
\end{definition}


